I is left as-is, not part of the schema answer -->\n                                          <\/div>\n                  <\/dd>\n                              <\/div>\n                          <!-- Each FAQ item is a Question, linked via mainEntity -->\n              <div class=\"accordion-item\" data-cursor=\"hover\" itemprop=\"mainEntity\" itemscope itemtype=\"https:\/\/schema.org\/Question\">\n                                  <dt class=\"accordion-item-title\">\n                    <h4 class=\"long\" itemprop=\"name\">Can the SEO Checker detect all SEO issues?<\/h4>\n                    <div class=\"icon\"><\/div>\n                  <\/dt>\n                \n                                  <dd class=\"accordion-item-content\">\n                    <div class=\"accordion-item-content-inner wysiwyg\">\n                      <!-- Accepted answer content -->\n                      <div itemprop=\"acceptedAnswer\" itemscope itemtype=\"https:\/\/schema.org\/Answer\">\n                        <div itemprop=\"text\">\n                          <p>It is effective for common issues like missing meta data, slow pages, or broken links, but it will not catch everything. Complex, strategic, or niche issues are better handled manually.<\/p>\n                        <\/div>\n                      <\/div>\n\n                      <!-- Feedback UI is left as-is, not part of the schema answer -->\n                                          <\/div>\n                  <\/dd>\n                              <\/div>\n                          <!-- Each FAQ item is a Question, linked via mainEntity -->\n              <div class=\"accordion-item\" data-cursor=\"hover\" itemprop=\"mainEntity\" itemscope itemtype=\"https:\/\/schema.org\/Question\">\n                                  <dt class=\"accordion-item-title\">\n                    <h4 class=\"long\" itemprop=\"name\">Will the SEO Checker show me how to fix the issues it finds?<\/h4>\n                    <div class=\"icon\"><\/div>\n                  <\/dt>\n                \n                                  <dd class=\"accordion-item-content\">\n                    <div class=\"accordion-item-content-inner wysiwyg\">\n                      <!-- Accepted answer content -->\n                      <div itemprop=\"acceptedAnswer\" itemscope itemtype=\"https:\/\/schema.org\/Answer\">\n                        <div itemprop=\"text\">\n                          <p>Yes. It flags problems with practical suggestions. If you prefer, we can implement fixes for you.<\/p>\n                        <\/div>\n                      <\/div>\n\n                      <!-- Feedback UI is left as-is, not part of the schema answer -->\n                                          <\/div>\n                  <\/dd>\n                              <\/div>\n                          <!-- Each FAQ item is a Question, linked via mainEntity -->\n              <div class=\"accordion-item\" data-cursor=\"hover\" itemprop=\"mainEntity\" itemscope itemtype=\"https:\/\/schema.org\/Question\">\n                                  <dt class=\"accordion-item-title\">\n                    <h4 class=\"long\" itemprop=\"name\">Does the SEO Checker work for all website platforms?<\/h4>\n                    <div class=\"icon\"><\/div>\n                  <\/dt>\n                \n                                  <dd class=\"accordion-item-content\">\n                    <div class=\"accordion-item-content-inner wysiwyg\">\n                      <!-- Accepted answer content -->\n                      <div itemprop=\"acceptedAnswer\" itemscope itemtype=\"https:\/\/schema.org\/Answer\">\n                        <div itemprop=\"text\">\n                          <p>Yes. It works with WordPress, Shopify, Wix, and most major platforms by checking universal SEO factors such as meta tags, speed, and mobile experience.<\/p>\n                        <\/div>\n                      <\/div>\n\n                      <!-- Feedback UI is left as-is, not part of the schema answer -->\n                                          <\/div>\n                  <\/dd>\n                              <\/div>\n                          <!-- Each FAQ item is a Question, linked via mainEntity -->\n              <div class=\"accordion-item\" data-cursor=\"hover\" itemprop=\"mainEntity\" itemscope itemtype=\"https:\/\/schema.org\/Question\">\n                                  <dt class=\"accordion-item-title\">\n                    <h4 class=\"long\" itemprop=\"name\">Should I rely on an SEO Checker or hire an SEO expert?<\/h4>\n                    <div class=\"icon\"><\/div>\n                  <\/dt>\n                \n                                  <dd class=\"accordion-item-content\">\n                    <div class=\"accordion-item-content-inner wysiwyg\">\n                      <!-- Accepted answer content -->\n                      <div itemprop=\"acceptedAnswer\" itemscope itemtype=\"https:\/\/schema.org\/Answer\">\n                        <div itemprop=\"text\">\n                          <p>Use the checker as a starting point. For ongoing gains or complex challenges, an experienced SEO team will deliver more meaningful results. Both together work best.<\/p>\n                        <\/div>\n                      <\/div>\n\n                      <!-- Feedback UI is left as-is, not part of the schema answer -->\n                                          <\/div>\n                  <\/dd>\n                              <\/div>\n                      <\/dl>\n        <\/div>\n          <\/div>\n  <\/div>\n<\/section>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"parent":0,"menu_order":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"","meta":{"_acf_changed":false,"footnotes":""},"class_list":["post-5275","page","type-page","status-publish","hentry"],"acf":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.cbwebsitedesign.co.uk\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/5275","targetHints"